---
import * as Data from './Destinations.md'
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'

import DestinationsImage from './images/destinations.jpg'
import AmalfiImage from './images/amalfi.jpg'
import BernImage from './images/bern.jpg'
import SantoriniImage from './images/santorini.jpg'
import BarcelonaImage from './images/barcelona.jpg'
import ReykjavikImage from './images/reykjavik.jpg'
import EtnaImage from './images/etna.jpg'
import FiordsImage from './images/fiords.jpg'
import RomeImage from './images/rome.jpg'
---

<section id="destinations" class="destinations">
  <div class="destinations-container">
    <div class="destinations-header">
      <h2 class="destinations-title">{Data.frontmatter.title}</h2>
      <span class="destinations-subtitle">{Data.frontmatter.subtitle}</span>
      <Image class="destinations-image" src={DestinationsImage} alt="" />
    </div>
    <div class="accordion">
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">
          <h3 class="accordion-title">Amalfi</h3>
          <span class="accordion-subtitle">Italy</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <Image class="accordion-content__image" src={AmalfiImage} alt="" />
          <p>A helicopter tour over the volcanic island of Ischia in the Gulf of Naples is a unique opportunity to see this beautiful region from a bird's eye view. This island was inhabited by people back in the days of the Phoenicians, and even then everyone was amazed by its beauty. During the tour, you will see many of Italy's landmarks. You will fly over the rocky island of Capri, over the Amalfi Coast, over modern Naples and ancient Pompeii and Herculaneum - two cities once buried under the ashes of Vesuvius. This route will allow you to enjoy magnificent views of the mountains, volcanoes, coasts and cities. You will be able to see all these beauties from a completely new perspective.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">
          <h3 class="accordion-title">Bern-Belp</h3>
          <span class="accordion-subtitle">Switzerland</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <Image class="accordion-content__image" src={BernImage} alt="" />
          <p>Enjoy a helicopter flight from the Swiss capital and combine the trip with a visit to the historic old town of Bern. Or combine your helicopter flight with a visit to the beautifully located city of Thun, which can be reached by car in 20 minutes from the airport.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">
          <h3 class="accordion-title">Santorini</h3>
          <span class="accordion-subtitle">Greece</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <Image class="accordion-content__image" src={SantoriniImage} alt="" />
          <p>Santorini is an island in Greece, famous for its whitewashed houses, blue-domed churches and breathtaking landscapes. A helicopter tour over Santorini is a unique way to see this island from a bird's eye view. The tour starts from Santorini airport, from where the helicopter takes off towards the center of the island. During the flight, tourists can enjoy magnificent views of the volcanic caldera that surrounds the island, as well as the white houses located on the hillsides. Approaching the center of the island, the helicopter begins to circle around the main attractions, allowing the tour participants to see all their beauty. The churches with blue domes that stand out against the background of white houses look especially impressive. In addition, tourists can see various landforms formed by volcanic activity: rocky shores, beaches with black sand and other geological formations. A helicopter tour over Santorini is an unforgettable experience for nature and culture lovers. It allows you to see the beauty and diversity of this island from a completely new perspective.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">
          <h3 class="accordion-title">Barcelona</h3>
          <span class="accordion-subtitle">Spain</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <Image class="accordion-content__image" src={BarcelonaImage} alt="" />
          <p>See Barcelona from every angle in just half a day on this walking, boat, and helicopter tour, perfect for a quick, yet comprehensive overview of the city. Stroll the Gothic Quarter and other must-sees with a guide, cruise along the coastline, and enjoy a short helicopter sightseeing ride, something that's usually very expensive when done on your own. A choice of departure times provides the flexibility you need on vacation</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">
          <h3 class="accordion-title">Reykjavik</h3>
          <span class="accordion-subtitle">Island</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <Image class="accordion-content__image" src={ReykjavikImage} alt="" />
          <p>Reykjavik is the capital of Iceland, located on the Seltjadnarnes Peninsula. The city is known for its geothermal springs and proximity to volcanoes. A helicopter tour over the volcano in Reykjavik is a unique way to see this natural site from a bird's eye view. The tour starts from Reykjavik Airport, from where the helicopter takes off towards the volcano. During the flight, tourists can enjoy magnificent views of the city, as well as the surrounding mountains and glaciers. Having approached the volcano, the helicopter begins to circle around it, allowing the tour participants to see all its craters and lava flows. The active zone of the volcano, where ash and lava emissions occur, looks especially impressive. In addition, tourists can see various landforms formed by volcanic activity: lava fields, cones, calderas and other geological formations. A helicopter tour over the volcano in Reykjavik is an unforgettable experience for nature lovers and extreme sports enthusiasts. It allows you to see the beauty and power of nature from a completely new perspective.‚Äù</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">
          <h3 class="accordion-title">Etna Volcano</h3>
          <span class="accordion-subtitle">Italy</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <Image class="accordion-content__image" src={EtnaImage} alt="" />
          <p>Mount Etna is the highest active volcano in Europe. Its height is 3,329 meters. It is located on the island of Sicily in Italy. A helicopter tour over Mount Etna is a unique opportunity to see this natural object from a bird's eye view. The tour starts from Catania Airport, from where the helicopter departs towards the volcano. During the flight, tourists can enjoy magnificent views of the Ionian coast, as well as the cities of Catania and Taormina. Having approached the volcano, the helicopter begins to circle around it, allowing the tour participants to see all its craters and lava flows. The active zone of the volcano, where ash and lava emissions occur, looks especially impressive. In addition, tourists can see various landforms formed by volcanic activity: lava fields, cones, calderas and other geological formations. A helicopter tour over Mount Etna is an unforgettable experience for nature lovers and extreme sports enthusiasts. It allows you to see the beauty and power of nature from a completely new perspective.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">
          <h3 class="accordion-title">Fiords</h3>
          <span class="accordion-subtitle">Norway</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <Image class="accordion-content__image" src={FiordsImage} alt="" />
          <p>The fjords of Norway are one of the most picturesque places on the planet. They are narrow sea bays surrounded by high cliffs. A helicopter tour over the fjords is a unique way to see this beauty from a bird's eye view. The tour starts from Bergen or Oslo airport, from where the helicopter takes off towards the fjords. During the flight, tourists can enjoy magnificent views of mountain peaks, glaciers and waterfalls. Having approached the fjords, the helicopter begins to circle around them, allowing the tour participants to see all their beauty. Particularly impressive are the narrow passages between the rocks, where the water forms small waterfalls. In addition, tourists can see various landforms formed by glacial activity: valleys, lakes, glacial deposits and other geological formations. A helicopter tour over the fjords in Norway is an unforgettable experience for nature lovers and extreme sports enthusiasts. It allows you to see the beauty and power of nature from a completely new perspective.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">
          <h3 class="accordion-title">Rome</h3>
          <span class="accordion-subtitle">Italy</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <Image class="accordion-content__image" src={RomeImage} alt="" />
          <p>Rome is one of the most ancient cities in the world, famous for its rich history and cultural heritage. A helicopter tour over Rome is a unique way to see this city from a bird's eye view. The tour starts from Rome airport, from where the helicopter takes off towards the city center. During the flight, tourists can enjoy magnificent views of historical monuments such as the Colosseum, the Pantheon and the Vatican. Approaching the city center, the helicopter begins to circle around the main attractions, allowing tour participants to see all their beauty. Ancient ruins such as the Forum Romanum and the Baths of Caracalla look especially impressive. In addition, tourists can see various forms of urban development formed in different eras: medieval streets, baroque squares and modern skyscrapers. A helicopter tour over Rome is an unforgettable experience for lovers of history and architecture. It allows you to see the beauty and diversity of this city from a completely new perspective.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const accordionHeaders = document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-header');

    accordionHeaders.forEach(header => {
      header.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const accordionItem = header.parentElement;
        if (!accordionItem) return;
        const isActive = accordionItem.classList.contains('active');

        document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-item.active').forEach(item => {
          item.classList.remove('active');
          const content = item.querySelector('.accordion-content') as HTMLElement;

          if (content) {
            content.style.maxHeight = '0';
          }
        });

        if (!isActive) {
          accordionItem.classList.add('active');
          const accordionContent = accordionItem.querySelector('.accordion-content') as HTMLElement;
          if (accordionContent) {
            accordionContent.style.maxHeight = accordionContent.scrollHeight + 'px';
          }
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>

<style lang="scss">
  @import './Destinations.scss';
</style>
